 * MemoryRecords does not own the backing ByteBuffer; the caller is responsible for:
 * <ul>
 *   <li>Keeping the buffer valid during MemoryRecords' lifetime</li>
 *   <li>Releasing/deallocating the buffer when no longer needed</li>
 *   <li>Avoiding modifications to the buffer while iteration is in progress</li>
 * </ul>
 *
 * <p><strong>Performance Characteristics:</strong>
 * <ul>
 *   <li><strong>Lazy Batch Parsing:</strong> Batches are decoded on-demand during iteration.</li>
 *   <li><strong>Valid Bytes Caching:</strong> {@link #validBytes()} is computed once and cached;
